\par }{\f2\fs28\insrsid4007541 It may be difficult for your teenage child to make healthy choices when they are }{\f2\fs28\insrsid12935806 at }{\f2\fs28\insrsid4007541 school}{\f2\fs28\insrsid12935806 ,}{\f2\fs28\insrsid4007541 
 as often the hallways are lined with vending machines, but it is possible.  Why not try and encourage them to replace }{\f2\fs28\insrsid3821150 even one bag of chips each day with a much hea
lthier grab and go option from home, such as frozen grapes, an orange, st}{\f2\fs28\insrsid12935806 rawberries or other fresh fruit?}{\f2\fs28\insrsid3821150   They may even like to take some sliced red, orange or yellow peppers}{\f2\fs28\insrsid12935806 
,}{\f2\fs28\insrsid3821150  a few cherry tomatoes or baby carrots instead.  }{\f2\fs28\insrsid4007541 
